  abstract = {C-systems were introduced by J. Cartmell under the name "contextual categories". In this note we study sub-objects and quotient-objects of C-systems. In the case of the sub-objects we consider all sub-objects while in the case of the quotient-objects only \textbraceleft\textbackslash em regular\textbraceright{} quotients that in particular have the property that the corresponding projection morphism is surjective both on objects and on morphisms. It is one of several short papers based on the material of the "Notes on Type Systems" by the same author. This version is essentially identical with the version published in Contemporary Mathematics n.658.},
